                                                      Vdev - Virtual Devices
How do vdevs relate to storage pools?
Vdevs are the building blocks of ZFS storage pools.
A storage pool (zpool) is created by combining one or more top-level vdevs.
The overall performance, capacity, and redundancy of the storage pool depend on the configuration and types of vdevs used.

"Taken from: https://openzfs.github.io/openzfs-docs/Basic%20Concepts/VDEVs.html"


