The Nordix installer will create a clone of your system which is recommended to use
and let the original boot environment left untouched

then you always have a default to return to, like a system restore
you can do this without affecting your home. 

If you need multiple users on your PC
the recommended way in Nordix is not to create multiple users
but instead create a clone of the system and then have separate boot environments,
It may be necessary to adapt mounting home with legacy mountpoint to not mix up your homes.

The system base snapshots will allow you to create as many different boot environments as you want.

Creating a new boot environment "BE" with ZFS clones does not take up any extra disk space
you can think of ZFS clones as a virtual boot environment

It is perfectly possible to create multiple BEs for different purposes
one for Gaming, one for Virtual machines, one for local AI, etc. 
This is one of the major advantages of ZFS.

New boot environments, system rollback, creating full boot environments from snapshots is easy to do directly from zfsbootmenu.
Nordix comes with an automatic snapshot system, so you are always ready to quickly restore your system or create new BE

